00:53:46.117 --> 00:53:47.200
DAVID THORBURN: All right.

00:53:47.200 --> 00:53:50.890
So you can get an idea not
only for how richly comic

00:53:50.890 --> 00:53:54.990
these films can be, but
also how rich the subtext,

00:53:54.990 --> 00:53:57.180
the sexual subtext can become.

00:53:57.180 --> 00:53:58.990
Even though, of
course, as you all

00:53:58.990 --> 00:54:01.300
should know if you've
been reading Cook,

00:54:01.300 --> 00:54:05.340
there was a production
code in force after 1934,

00:54:05.340 --> 00:54:08.180
and there were all kinds of
very elaborate rules imposed

00:54:08.180 --> 00:54:09.680
on American movies.

00:54:09.680 --> 00:54:13.032
A form of self censorship
because the movies feared

00:54:13.032 --> 00:54:14.990
censorship from the
government, so they came up

00:54:14.990 --> 00:54:16.090
with their own system.

00:54:16.090 --> 00:54:17.860
And until sometime
in the, I guess

00:54:17.860 --> 00:54:23.610
it was the 1960's, the code
held and it had all kinds

00:54:23.610 --> 00:54:25.140
of ridiculous elements in it.

00:54:25.140 --> 00:54:27.660
One of the primary ones that
people always laugh about,

00:54:27.660 --> 00:54:30.510
rightly I think, is that if
it showed a woman on a bed,

00:54:30.510 --> 00:54:33.094
at least one of her feet
had to be on the floor.

00:54:33.094 --> 00:54:35.510
You couldn't show a woman lying
with both feet on the bed,

00:54:35.510 --> 00:54:37.260
it was too suggestive.

00:54:37.260 --> 00:54:39.410
But you can see how
clever filmmakers

00:54:39.410 --> 00:54:41.840
and powerful performers
were able to make

00:54:41.840 --> 00:54:44.760
a mockery of those
kinds of constraints,

00:54:44.760 --> 00:54:49.300
because subtle and complex
and witty films are

00:54:49.300 --> 00:54:51.120
able to do many,
many things that

00:54:51.120 --> 00:54:54.760
are in a suggestive way,
that keep them from crossing

00:54:54.760 --> 00:54:57.680
the boundaries set
up by the censors,

00:54:57.680 --> 00:55:01.310
but nonetheless have a
powerful energy and sexuality.

00:55:03.930 --> 00:55:08.120
So the similarities
between those two scenes,

00:55:08.120 --> 00:55:10.050
but also the differences
between them,

00:55:10.050 --> 00:55:13.800
tell you something
about the way in which

00:55:13.800 --> 00:55:17.890
the aesthetic of connection,
this aesthetic of familiarity,

00:55:17.890 --> 00:55:22.490
this popular aesthetic
operated in Hollywood movies.

